The paper deals with the problem of sampling permutations and analyzing the mixing rate of a specific Markov chain. This falls under the category of probability and statistics (cs.PR) and also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and graph theory (cs.GT) to analyze the mixing rate. Additionally, the paper discusses the "Choose Your Weapon" and "League Hierarchies" classes, which are related to game theory and machine learning, respectively, and could potentially fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) or game theory (cs.GT).
